			"leadParagraph": "Los Angeles based Iya Terra makes funky roots reggae music for the modern world. With an emphasis on spreading love and positivity, they embody the spirit of traditional roots reggae bysinging about anti-establishment and simple living. Iya Terra, which translates to 'higher ground,' came to life in 2013 when friends Nathan Feinstein (vocals, guitar) and Nick Loporchio (bassist) started singing songs of positivity to the masses on the streets of Los Angeles. They filled out their sound by adding Danny Monar (percussion), Luis Tovar (keys), Blake Bartz (drums) and finally in 2015, Nick Sefakis (rhythm guitar). Iya Terra released their self titled EP in 2014, produced by award winning engineer JP Hesser and recorded at Castaway 7 Studios. Soon after, in the spring of 2015, they put out their debut album, Full Circle, which included collaborations with artists such as Dub Architect, Corey Draskovich and Karim Israel. From there they went on tour and have since shared the stage with greats such as Yellow Man, Ital Vibes, Collie Buddz, Fortunate Youth, Ky-Mani Marley, Easy Star All Stars and Barrington Levy. Their sophomore album, Sacred Sound, debuted at #1 on the iTunes reggae charts in 2017 and solidified their position in the modern roots reggae scene. Coming to Light, their most recent album, was released in 2019 and featured collaborations with The Movement, Satsang, The Green and Cas Haley. Slated to play both the California Roots Festival 2020 and Rise Up Music Festival Vegas 2020 this year, the band shows no signs of slowing down. Earlier this spring they put out a 'Live at Sugar Shack Sessions' LP and their new single Outer Space, produced by reggae powerhouse Stick Figure, dropped on June 19th.",
